Set up the Django messaging app locally
1.Locate your messaging_app project

This is the project you built during Building Robust APIs.

Example structure:
Documents/
   └── messaging_app/
        ├── manage.py
        ├── config/
        ├── apps/
        └── requirements.txt
2.Make a full copy of this directory

If you're using a GUI (Windows Explorer / Finder):

Right-click → Copy

Right-click → Paste

Rename the new folder

If you're using terminal (recommended):
cp -r messaging_app Django-Middleware-0x03

This creates:
Django-Middleware-0x03/

3.Verify the copy

Inside your new folder, you should still see:
Django-Middleware-0x03/
├── manage.py
├── config/
├── apps/
└── requirements.txt

4.Optional but Recommended: Create a new virtual environment

Inside the new folder:
python -m venv venv

Activate it:

Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate

Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

5.Install dependencies

Inside your virtual environment:
pip install -r requirements.txt

6.Run the server to verify everything works
python manage.py runserver



